# Verify Build After Changes

After editing Java code or Gradle build files, **always run a build** to ensure the project compiles.

## When to Run

- After modifying any `.java` file
- After changing `build.gradle`, `build.gradle.kts`, `settings.gradle`, or `gradle.properties`
- After adding, removing, or updating dependencies

## Command

```bash
./gradlew build
```

Or for a quicker compile-only check:

```bash
./gradlew compileJava
```

## Expectations

- Build must succeed (exit code 0) before considering the change complete
- Fix any compilation errors before finishing
- If tests exist, `./gradlew build` will run them; fix failing tests as well
